      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROYAL OPTIMISM (4) can break through third up. He's placed in both runs back, finding the line strongly at Yarra Valley second up over 1958m, beaten at $1.70 but not disgraced on a track that's tough to make ground. Lane goes aboard, he can improve again and get the job done. TRYST AND DOUBT (6) is coming along well in his first campaign, just finding one better at Ballarat last start when edged out by a nose. He maps for a great run on speed and takes plenty of catching. SOUL MISTRESS (7) is knocking on the door, placing in her past couple. She comes back slightly in trip from 2500m last time but will be strong late. PARAMOUNT WAR (3) is going well but has had a few chances. He maps for a nice run.",
